# Python style

Write Python that is easy to learn from.

Rules:
- Use pathlib instead of os.path where practical.
- Prefer dataclasses or TypedDict over ad-hoc dicts for structured data.
- Keep functions under ~40 lines when possible.
- Separate concerns:
  - ingestion
  - indexing
  - retrieval
  - generation
  - evaluation
  - UI
- Avoid deeply nested logic.
- Add comments only when they help understanding.
- Prefer explicit names over abbreviations.
- Preserve imports order and remove unused imports.
